## What are Validations?

Validations ensure data integrity before saving to the database. They run before `create`, `save`, and `update`.

```ruby
class Article < ApplicationRecord
  validates :title, presence: true
end

article = Article.new
article.save  # false (validation failed)
article.errors.full_messages  # ["Title can't be blank"]
```

